22#define ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(DST, SRC, PROPERTY) \
23 (DST).PROPERTY = static_cast<__typeof__((DST).PROPERTY)>(ToObjC((SRC).PROPERTY))
24
25#define ANGLE_PROP_EQ(LHS, RHS, PROP) ((LHS).PROP == (RHS).PROP)

35template <class T>
36inline T ToObjC(const T p)
37{
38 return p;
39}
40
41inline MTLStencilDescriptor *ToObjC(const StencilDesc &desc)
42{
43 MTLStencilDescriptor *objCDesc = [[MTLStencilDescriptor alloc] init];
44
45 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, stencilFailureOperation);
46 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, depthFailureOperation);
47 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, depthStencilPassOperation);
48 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, stencilCompareFunction);
49 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, readMask);
50 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, writeMask);
51
52 return [objCDesc ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
53}

64 return [objCDesc ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];

100

107
108MTLVertexDescriptor *ToObjC(const VertexDesc &desc)
109{
110 MTLVertexDescriptor *objCDesc = [[MTLVertexDescriptor alloc] init];
111 [objCDesc reset];
112
113 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < desc.numAttribs; ++i)
114 {
115 [objCDesc.attributes setObject:ToObjC(desc.attributes[i]) atIndexedSubscript:i];
116 }
117
118 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < desc.numBufferLayouts; ++i)
119 {
120 // Ignore if stepFunction is kVertexStepFunctionInvalid.
121 // If we don't set this slot, it will apparently be disabled by metal runtime.
122 if (desc.layouts[i].stepFunction != kVertexStepFunctionInvalid)
123 {
124 [objCDesc.layouts setObject:ToObjC(desc.layouts[i]) atIndexedSubscript:i];
125 }
126 }
127
128 return [objCDesc ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
129}

131MTLRenderPipelineColorAttachmentDescriptor *ToObjC(const RenderPipelineColorAttachmentDesc &desc)
132{
133 MTLRenderPipelineColorAttachmentDescriptor *objCDesc =
134 [[MTLRenderPipelineColorAttachmentDescriptor alloc] init];
135
136 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, pixelFormat);
137 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, writeMask);
138 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, alphaBlendOperation);
139 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, rgbBlendOperation);
140 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, destinationAlphaBlendFactor);
141 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, destinationRGBBlendFactor);
142 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, sourceAlphaBlendFactor);
143 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, sourceRGBBlendFactor);
144 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, blendingEnabled);
145
146 return [objCDesc ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];

148
149MTLRenderPipelineDescriptor *ToObjC(id<MTLFunction> vertexShader,
150 id<MTLFunction> fragmentShader,
151 const RenderPipelineDesc &desc)
152{
153 MTLRenderPipelineDescriptor *objCDesc = [[MTLRenderPipelineDescriptor alloc] init];
154 [objCDesc reset];
155
156 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, vertexDescriptor);
157
158 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < desc.outputDescriptor.numColorAttachments; ++i)
159 {
160 [objCDesc.colorAttachments setObject:ToObjC(desc.outputDescriptor.colorAttachments[i])
161 atIndexedSubscript:i];
162 }
163 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc.outputDescriptor, depthAttachmentPixelFormat);
164 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc.outputDescriptor, stencilAttachmentPixelFormat);
165 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc.outputDescriptor, sampleCount);
166
167#if ANGLE_MTL_PRIMITIVE_TOPOLOGY_CLASS_AVAILABLE
168 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, inputPrimitiveTopology);
169#endif
170 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(objCDesc, desc, alphaToCoverageEnabled);
171
172 // rasterizationEnabled will be true for both EmulatedDiscard & Enabled.
173 objCDesc.rasterizationEnabled = desc.rasterizationEnabled();
174
175 objCDesc.vertexFunction = vertexShader;
176 objCDesc.fragmentFunction = objCDesc.rasterizationEnabled ? fragmentShader : nil;
177
178 return [objCDesc ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
179}
180
181id<MTLTexture> ToObjC(const TextureRef &texture)
182{
183 auto textureRef = texture;
184 return textureRef ? textureRef->get() : nil;
185}
186
187void BaseRenderPassAttachmentDescToObjC(MTLRenderPassAttachmentDescriptor *dst,
188 const RenderPassAttachmentDesc &src)
189{
190 auto implicitMsTexture = src.implicitMSTexture();
191
192 if (implicitMsTexture)
193 {
194 dst.texture = ToObjC(implicitMsTexture);
195 dst.level = 0;
196 dst.slice = 0;
197 dst.depthPlane = 0;
198 dst.resolveTexture = ToObjC(src.texture());
199 dst.resolveLevel = src.level().get();
200 if (dst.resolveTexture.textureType == MTLTextureType3D)
201 {
202 dst.resolveDepthPlane = src.sliceOrDepth();
203 dst.resolveSlice = 0;
204 }
205 else
206 {
207 dst.resolveSlice = src.sliceOrDepth();
208 dst.resolveDepthPlane = 0;
209 }
210 }
211 else
212 {
213 dst.texture = ToObjC(src.texture());
214 dst.level = src.level().get();
215 if (dst.texture.textureType == MTLTextureType3D)
216 {
217 dst.depthPlane = src.sliceOrDepth();
218 dst.slice = 0;
219 }
220 else
221 {
222 dst.slice = src.sliceOrDepth();
223 dst.depthPlane = 0;
224 }
225 dst.resolveTexture = nil;
226 dst.resolveLevel = 0;
227 dst.resolveSlice = 0;
228 dst.resolveDepthPlane = 0;
229 }
230
231 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(dst, src, loadAction);
232 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(dst, src, storeAction);
233 ANGLE_OBJC_CP_PROPERTY(dst, src, storeActionOptions);
234}
235

262// StencilDesc implementation
263bool StencilDesc::operator==(const StencilDesc &rhs) const
264{
265 return ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, stencilFailureOperation) &&
266 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, depthFailureOperation) &&
267 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, depthStencilPassOperation) &&
268
269 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, stencilCompareFunction) &&
270
271 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, readMask) && ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, writeMask);
272}
273
274void StencilDesc::reset()
275{
276 stencilFailureOperation = depthFailureOperation = depthStencilPassOperation =
277 MTLStencilOperationKeep;
278
279 stencilCompareFunction = MTLCompareFunctionAlways;
280 readMask = writeMask = std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() & mtl::kStencilMaskAll;
281}

284DepthStencilDesc::DepthStencilDesc()

286 memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this));

288DepthStencilDesc::DepthStencilDesc(const DepthStencilDesc &src)

290 memcpy(this, &src, sizeof(*this));

296

299 memcpy(this, &src, sizeof(*this));
300 return *this;
301}
302
303bool DepthStencilDesc::operator==(const DepthStencilDesc &rhs) const
304{
305 return ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, backFaceStencil) &&
306 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, frontFaceStencil) &&
307
308 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, depthCompareFunction) &&
309
310 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, depthWriteEnabled);
311}
312
313void DepthStencilDesc::reset()
314{
315 frontFaceStencil.reset();
316 backFaceStencil.reset();
317
318 depthCompareFunction = MTLCompareFunctionAlways;
319 depthWriteEnabled = true;
320}
321
322void DepthStencilDesc::updateDepthTestEnabled(const gl::DepthStencilState &dsState)
323{
324 if (!dsState.depthTest)
325 {
326 depthCompareFunction = MTLCompareFunctionAlways;
327 depthWriteEnabled = false;
328 }
329 else
330 {
331 updateDepthCompareFunc(dsState);
332 updateDepthWriteEnabled(dsState);
333 }
334}
335
336void DepthStencilDesc::updateDepthWriteEnabled(const gl::DepthStencilState &dsState)
337{
338 depthWriteEnabled = dsState.depthTest && dsState.depthMask;
339}
340
341void DepthStencilDesc::updateDepthCompareFunc(const gl::DepthStencilState &dsState)
342{
343 if (!dsState.depthTest)
344 {
345 return;
346 }
347 depthCompareFunction = GetCompareFunc(dsState.depthFunc);
348}
349
350void DepthStencilDesc::updateStencilTestEnabled(const gl::DepthStencilState &dsState)
351{
352 if (!dsState.stencilTest)
353 {
354 frontFaceStencil.stencilCompareFunction = MTLCompareFunctionAlways;
355 frontFaceStencil.depthFailureOperation = MTLStencilOperationKeep;
356 frontFaceStencil.depthStencilPassOperation = MTLStencilOperationKeep;
357 frontFaceStencil.writeMask = 0;
358
359 backFaceStencil.stencilCompareFunction = MTLCompareFunctionAlways;
360 backFaceStencil.depthFailureOperation = MTLStencilOperationKeep;
361 backFaceStencil.depthStencilPassOperation = MTLStencilOperationKeep;
362 backFaceStencil.writeMask = 0;
363 }
364 else
365 {
366 updateStencilFrontFuncs(dsState);
367 updateStencilFrontOps(dsState);
368 updateStencilFrontWriteMask(dsState);
369 updateStencilBackFuncs(dsState);
370 updateStencilBackOps(dsState);
371 updateStencilBackWriteMask(dsState);
372 }
373}
374
375void DepthStencilDesc::updateStencilFrontOps(const gl::DepthStencilState &dsState)
376{
377 if (!dsState.stencilTest)
378 {
379 return;
380 }
381 frontFaceStencil.stencilFailureOperation = GetStencilOp(dsState.stencilFail);
382 frontFaceStencil.depthFailureOperation = GetStencilOp(dsState.stencilPassDepthFail);
383 frontFaceStencil.depthStencilPassOperation = GetStencilOp(dsState.stencilPassDepthPass);
384}
385
386void DepthStencilDesc::updateStencilBackOps(const gl::DepthStencilState &dsState)
387{
388 if (!dsState.stencilTest)
389 {
390 return;
391 }
392 backFaceStencil.stencilFailureOperation = GetStencilOp(dsState.stencilBackFail);
393 backFaceStencil.depthFailureOperation = GetStencilOp(dsState.stencilBackPassDepthFail);
394 backFaceStencil.depthStencilPassOperation = GetStencilOp(dsState.stencilBackPassDepthPass);
395}
396
397void DepthStencilDesc::updateStencilFrontFuncs(const gl::DepthStencilState &dsState)
398{
399 if (!dsState.stencilTest)
400 {
401 return;
402 }
403 frontFaceStencil.stencilCompareFunction = GetCompareFunc(dsState.stencilFunc);
404 frontFaceStencil.readMask = dsState.stencilMask & mtl::kStencilMaskAll;
405}
406
407void DepthStencilDesc::updateStencilBackFuncs(const gl::DepthStencilState &dsState)
408{
409 if (!dsState.stencilTest)
410 {
411 return;
412 }
413 backFaceStencil.stencilCompareFunction = GetCompareFunc(dsState.stencilBackFunc);
414 backFaceStencil.readMask = dsState.stencilBackMask & mtl::kStencilMaskAll;
415}
416
417void DepthStencilDesc::updateStencilFrontWriteMask(const gl::DepthStencilState &dsState)
418{
419 if (!dsState.stencilTest)
420 {
421 return;
422 }
423 frontFaceStencil.writeMask = dsState.stencilWritemask & mtl::kStencilMaskAll;
424}
425
426void DepthStencilDesc::updateStencilBackWriteMask(const gl::DepthStencilState &dsState)
427{
428 if (!dsState.stencilTest)
429 {
430 return;
431 }
432 backFaceStencil.writeMask = dsState.stencilBackWritemask & mtl::kStencilMaskAll;
433}

437 return angle::ComputeGenericHash(*this);
438}

440// SamplerDesc implementation
441SamplerDesc::SamplerDesc()
442{
443 memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this));
444}
445SamplerDesc::SamplerDesc(const SamplerDesc &src)
446{
447 memcpy(this, &src, sizeof(*this));
448}
449SamplerDesc::SamplerDesc(SamplerDesc &&src)
450{
451 memcpy(this, &src, sizeof(*this));
452}
453
454SamplerDesc::SamplerDesc(const gl::SamplerState &glState) : SamplerDesc()
455{
456 rAddressMode = GetSamplerAddressMode(glState.getWrapR());
457 sAddressMode = GetSamplerAddressMode(glState.getWrapS());
458 tAddressMode = GetSamplerAddressMode(glState.getWrapT());
459
460 minFilter = GetFilter(glState.getMinFilter());
461 magFilter = GetFilter(glState.getMagFilter());
462 mipFilter = GetMipmapFilter(glState.getMinFilter());
463
464 maxAnisotropy = static_cast<uint32_t>(glState.getMaxAnisotropy());
465
466 compareFunction = GetCompareFunc(glState.getCompareFunc());
467
468 normalizedCoordinates = YES;
469}
470
471SamplerDesc &SamplerDesc::operator=(const SamplerDesc &src)
472{
473 memcpy(this, &src, sizeof(*this));
474 return *this;
475}
476
477void SamplerDesc::reset()
478{
479 rAddressMode = MTLSamplerAddressModeClampToEdge;
480 sAddressMode = MTLSamplerAddressModeClampToEdge;
481 tAddressMode = MTLSamplerAddressModeClampToEdge;
482
483 minFilter = MTLSamplerMinMagFilterNearest;
484 magFilter = MTLSamplerMinMagFilterNearest;
485 mipFilter = MTLSamplerMipFilterNearest;
486
487 maxAnisotropy = 1;
488
489 compareFunction = MTLCompareFunctionNever;
490
491 normalizedCoordinates = YES;
492}
493
494bool SamplerDesc::operator==(const SamplerDesc &rhs) const
495{
496 return ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, rAddressMode) && ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, sAddressMode) &&
497 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, tAddressMode) &&
498
499 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, minFilter) && ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, magFilter) &&
500 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, mipFilter) &&
501
502 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, maxAnisotropy) &&
503
504 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, compareFunction);
505}
506
507size_t SamplerDesc::hash() const
508{
509 return angle::ComputeGenericHash(*this);
510}

512// BlendDesc implementation
513bool BlendDesc::operator==(const BlendDesc &rhs) const
514{
515 return ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, writeMask) &&
516
517 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, alphaBlendOperation) &&
518 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, rgbBlendOperation) &&
519
520 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, destinationAlphaBlendFactor) &&
521 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, destinationRGBBlendFactor) &&
522 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, sourceAlphaBlendFactor) &&
523 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, sourceRGBBlendFactor) &&
524
525 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, blendingEnabled);
526}
527
528void BlendDesc::reset()
529{
530 reset(MTLColorWriteMaskAll);
531}
532
533void BlendDesc::reset(MTLColorWriteMask _writeMask)
534{
535 writeMask = _writeMask;
536
537 blendingEnabled = false;
538 alphaBlendOperation = rgbBlendOperation = MTLBlendOperationAdd;
539
540 destinationAlphaBlendFactor = destinationRGBBlendFactor = MTLBlendFactorZero;
541 sourceAlphaBlendFactor = sourceRGBBlendFactor = MTLBlendFactorOne;
542}
543
544void BlendDesc::updateWriteMask(const gl::BlendState &blendState)
545{
546 writeMask = MTLColorWriteMaskNone;
547 if (blendState.colorMaskRed)
548 {
549 writeMask |= MTLColorWriteMaskRed;
550 }
551 if (blendState.colorMaskGreen)
552 {
553 writeMask |= MTLColorWriteMaskGreen;
554 }
555 if (blendState.colorMaskBlue)
556 {
557 writeMask |= MTLColorWriteMaskBlue;
558 }
559 if (blendState.colorMaskAlpha)
560 {
561 writeMask |= MTLColorWriteMaskAlpha;
562 }
563}
564
565void BlendDesc::updateBlendFactors(const gl::BlendState &blendState)
566{
567 sourceRGBBlendFactor = GetBlendFactor(blendState.sourceBlendRGB);
568 sourceAlphaBlendFactor = GetBlendFactor(blendState.sourceBlendAlpha);
569 destinationRGBBlendFactor = GetBlendFactor(blendState.destBlendRGB);
570 destinationAlphaBlendFactor = GetBlendFactor(blendState.destBlendAlpha);
571}
572
573void BlendDesc::updateBlendOps(const gl::BlendState &blendState)
574{
575 rgbBlendOperation = GetBlendOp(blendState.blendEquationRGB);
576 alphaBlendOperation = GetBlendOp(blendState.blendEquationAlpha);
577}
578
579void BlendDesc::updateBlendEnabled(const gl::BlendState &blendState)
580{
581 blendingEnabled = blendState.blend;
582}

584// RenderPipelineColorAttachmentDesc implementation
585bool RenderPipelineColorAttachmentDesc::operator==(
586 const RenderPipelineColorAttachmentDesc &rhs) const
587{
588 if (!BlendDesc::operator==(rhs))
589 {
590 return false;
591 }
592 return ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, pixelFormat);
593}
594
595void RenderPipelineColorAttachmentDesc::reset()
596{
597 reset(MTLPixelFormatInvalid);
598}
599
600void RenderPipelineColorAttachmentDesc::reset(MTLPixelFormat format)
601{
602 reset(format, MTLColorWriteMaskAll);
603}
604
605void RenderPipelineColorAttachmentDesc::reset(MTLPixelFormat format, MTLColorWriteMask _writeMask)
606{
607 this->pixelFormat = format;
608
609 BlendDesc::reset(_writeMask);
610}
611
612void RenderPipelineColorAttachmentDesc::reset(MTLPixelFormat format, const BlendDesc &blendState)
613{
614 this->pixelFormat = format;
615
616 BlendDesc::operator=(blendState);
617}
618
619void RenderPipelineColorAttachmentDesc::update(const BlendDesc &blendState)
620{
621 BlendDesc::operator=(blendState);
622}
623
624// RenderPipelineOutputDesc implementation
625bool RenderPipelineOutputDesc::operator==(const RenderPipelineOutputDesc &rhs) const
626{
627 if (numColorAttachments != rhs.numColorAttachments)
628 {
629 return false;
630 }
631
632 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < numColorAttachments; ++i)
633 {
634 if (colorAttachments[i] != rhs.colorAttachments[i])
635 {
636 return false;
637 }
638 }
639
640 return ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, depthAttachmentPixelFormat) &&
641 ANGLE_PROP_EQ(*this, rhs, stencilAttachmentPixelFormat);
642}
643
644void RenderPipelineOutputDesc::updateEnabledDrawBuffers(gl::DrawBufferMask enabledBuffers)
645{
646 for (uint32_t colorIndex = 0; colorIndex < this->numColorAttachments; ++colorIndex)
647 {
648 if (!enabledBuffers.test(colorIndex))
649 {
650 this->colorAttachments[colorIndex].writeMask = MTLColorWriteMaskNone;
651 }
652 }
653}

678
679bool RenderPipelineDesc::operator==(const RenderPipelineDesc &rhs) const
680{
681 // NOTE(hqle): Use a faster way to compare, i.e take into account
682 // the number of active vertex attributes & render targets.
683 // If that way is used, hash() method must be changed also.
684 return memcmp(this, &rhs, sizeof(*this)) == 0;
685}

687size_t RenderPipelineDesc::hash() const
688{
689 return angle::ComputeGenericHash(*this);
690}
691
692bool RenderPipelineDesc::rasterizationEnabled() const
693{
694 return rasterizationType != RenderPipelineRasterization::Disabled;
695}
696
697// RenderPassDesc implementation
698RenderPassAttachmentDesc::RenderPassAttachmentDesc()
699{
700 reset();
701}
702
703void RenderPassAttachmentDesc::reset()
704{
705 renderTarget = nullptr;
706 loadAction = MTLLoadActionLoad;
707 storeAction = MTLStoreActionStore;
708 storeActionOptions = MTLStoreActionOptionNone;
709}
710
711bool RenderPassAttachmentDesc::equalIgnoreLoadStoreOptions(
712 const RenderPassAttachmentDesc &other) const
713{
714 return renderTarget == other.renderTarget ||
715 (texture() == other.texture() && level() == other.level() &&
716 sliceOrDepth() == other.sliceOrDepth());
717}

719bool RenderPassAttachmentDesc::operator==(const RenderPassAttachmentDesc &other) const
720{
721 if (!equalIgnoreLoadStoreOptions(other))
722 {
723 return false;
724 }
725
726 return loadAction == other.loadAction && storeAction == other.storeAction &&
727 storeActionOptions == other.storeActionOptions;
728}
729// Convert to Metal object
730void RenderPassDesc::convertToMetalDesc(MTLRenderPassDescriptor *objCDesc) const
731{
732 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
733 {
734 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numColorAttachments; ++i)
735 {
736 ToObjC(objCDesc.colorAttachments[i], colorAttachments[i]);
737 }
738 for (uint32_t i = numColorAttachments; i < kMaxRenderTargets; ++i)
739 {
740 // Inactive render target
741 objCDesc.colorAttachments[i].texture = nil;
742 objCDesc.colorAttachments[i].level = 0;
743 objCDesc.colorAttachments[i].slice = 0;
744 objCDesc.colorAttachments[i].depthPlane = 0;
745 objCDesc.colorAttachments[i].loadAction = MTLLoadActionDontCare;
746 objCDesc.colorAttachments[i].storeAction = MTLStoreActionDontCare;
747 }
748
749 ToObjC(objCDesc.depthAttachment, depthAttachment);
750 ToObjC(objCDesc.stencilAttachment, stencilAttachment);
751 }
752}
753
754void RenderPassDesc::populateRenderPipelineOutputDesc(RenderPipelineOutputDesc *outDesc) const
755{
756 populateRenderPipelineOutputDesc(MTLColorWriteMaskAll, outDesc);
757}
758
759void RenderPassDesc::populateRenderPipelineOutputDesc(MTLColorWriteMask colorWriteMask,
760 RenderPipelineOutputDesc *outDesc) const
761{
762 // Default blend state.
763 BlendDesc blendState;
764 blendState.reset(colorWriteMask);
765
766 populateRenderPipelineOutputDesc(blendState, outDesc);
767}
768
769void RenderPassDesc::populateRenderPipelineOutputDesc(const BlendDesc &blendState,
770 RenderPipelineOutputDesc *outDesc) const
771{
772 auto &outputDescriptor = *outDesc;
773 outputDescriptor.numColorAttachments = this->numColorAttachments;
774 outputDescriptor.sampleCount = this->sampleCount;
775 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < this->numColorAttachments; ++i)
776 {
777 auto &renderPassColorAttachment = this->colorAttachments[i];
778 auto texture = renderPassColorAttachment.texture();
779
780 if (texture)
781 {
782 // Copy parameters from blend state
783 outputDescriptor.colorAttachments[i].update(blendState);
784 if (!renderPassColorAttachment.blendable())
785 {
786 // Disable blending if the attachment's render target doesn't support blending.
787 outputDescriptor.colorAttachments[i].blendingEnabled = false;
788 }
789
790 outputDescriptor.colorAttachments[i].pixelFormat = texture->pixelFormat();
791
792 // Combine the masks. This is useful when the texture is not supposed to have alpha
793 // channel such as GL_RGB8, however, Metal doesn't natively support 24 bit RGB, so
794 // we need to use RGBA texture, and then disable alpha write to this texture
795 outputDescriptor.colorAttachments[i].writeMask &= texture->getColorWritableMask();
796 }
797 else
798 {
799
800 outputDescriptor.colorAttachments[i].blendingEnabled = false;
801 outputDescriptor.colorAttachments[i].pixelFormat = MTLPixelFormatInvalid;
802 }
803 }
804
805 // Reset the unused output slots to ensure consistent hash value
806 for (uint32_t i = this->numColorAttachments; i < kMaxRenderTargets; ++i)
807 {
808 outputDescriptor.colorAttachments[i].reset();
809 }
810
811 auto depthTexture = this->depthAttachment.texture();
812 outputDescriptor.depthAttachmentPixelFormat =
813 depthTexture ? depthTexture->pixelFormat() : MTLPixelFormatInvalid;
814
815 auto stencilTexture = this->stencilAttachment.texture();
816 outputDescriptor.stencilAttachmentPixelFormat =
817 stencilTexture ? stencilTexture->pixelFormat() : MTLPixelFormatInvalid;
818}
819
820bool RenderPassDesc::equalIgnoreLoadStoreOptions(const RenderPassDesc &other) const
821{
822 if (numColorAttachments != other.numColorAttachments)
823 {
824 return false;
825 }
826
827 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numColorAttachments; ++i)
828 {
829 auto &renderPassColorAttachment = colorAttachments[i];
830 auto &otherRPAttachment = other.colorAttachments[i];
831 if (!renderPassColorAttachment.equalIgnoreLoadStoreOptions(otherRPAttachment))
832 {
833 return false;
834 }
835 }
836
837 return depthAttachment.equalIgnoreLoadStoreOptions(other.depthAttachment) &&
838 stencilAttachment.equalIgnoreLoadStoreOptions(other.stencilAttachment);
839}
840
841bool RenderPassDesc::operator==(const RenderPassDesc &other) const
842{
843 if (numColorAttachments != other.numColorAttachments)
844 {
845 return false;
846 }
847
848 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < numColorAttachments; ++i)
849 {
850 auto &renderPassColorAttachment = colorAttachments[i];
851 auto &otherRPAttachment = other.colorAttachments[i];
852 if (renderPassColorAttachment != (otherRPAttachment))
853 {
854 return false;
855 }
856 }
857
858 return depthAttachment == other.depthAttachment && stencilAttachment == other.stencilAttachment;
859}

900bool RenderPipelineCache::hasDefaultAttribs(const RenderPipelineDesc &rpdesc) const
901{
902 const VertexDesc &desc = rpdesc.vertexDescriptor;
903 for (uint8_t i = 0; i < desc.numAttribs; ++i)
904 {
905 if (desc.attributes[i].bufferIndex == kDefaultAttribsBindingIndex)
906 {
907 return true;
908 }
909 }
910
911 return false;
912}

914AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLRenderPipelineState>> RenderPipelineCache::getRenderPipelineState(
915 ContextMtl *context,
916 const RenderPipelineDesc &desc)
917{
918 auto insertDefaultAttribLayout = hasDefaultAttribs(desc);
919 int tableIdx = insertDefaultAttribLayout ? 1 : 0;
920 auto &table = mRenderPipelineStates[tableIdx];
921 auto ite = table.find(desc);
922 if (ite == table.end())
923 {
924 return insertRenderPipelineState(context, desc, insertDefaultAttribLayout);
925 }
926
927 return ite->second;
928}

930AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLRenderPipelineState>> RenderPipelineCache::insertRenderPipelineState(
931 Context *context,
932 const RenderPipelineDesc &desc,
933 bool insertDefaultAttribLayout)
934{
935 AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLRenderPipelineState>> newState =
936 createRenderPipelineState(context, desc, insertDefaultAttribLayout);
937
938 int tableIdx = insertDefaultAttribLayout ? 1 : 0;
939 auto re = mRenderPipelineStates[tableIdx].insert(std::make_pair(desc, newState));
940 if (!re.second)
941 {
942 return nil;
943 }
944
945 return re.first->second;
946}

948
949AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLRenderPipelineState>> RenderPipelineCache::createRenderPipelineState(
950 Context *context,
951 const RenderPipelineDesc &originalDesc,
952 bool insertDefaultAttribLayout)
953{
954 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
955 {
956 // Disable coverage if the render pipeline's sample count is only 1.
957 RenderPipelineDesc desc = originalDesc;
958 if (desc.outputDescriptor.sampleCount == 1)
959 {
960 // Disable sample coverage if the output is not multisample
961 desc.emulateCoverageMask = false;
962 desc.alphaToCoverageEnabled = false;
963 }
964 // Choose shader variant
965 id<MTLFunction> vertShader = nil;
966 id<MTLFunction> fragShader = nil;
967 // Special case for transform feedback shader, we've already created it! See getTransformFeedbackRenderPipeline
968 if (desc.rasterizationType != mtl::RenderPipelineRasterization::Disabled &&
969 mSpecializedShaderFactory &&
970 mSpecializedShaderFactory->hasSpecializedShader(gl::ShaderType::Vertex, desc))
971 {
972 if (IsError(mSpecializedShaderFactory->getSpecializedShader(
973 context, gl::ShaderType::Vertex, desc, &vertShader)))
974 {
975 return nil;
976 }
977 }
978 else
979 {
980 // Non-specialized version
981 vertShader = mVertexShader;
982 }
983
984 if (mSpecializedShaderFactory &&
985 mSpecializedShaderFactory->hasSpecializedShader(gl::ShaderType::Fragment, desc))
986 {
987 if (IsError(mSpecializedShaderFactory->getSpecializedShader(
988 context, gl::ShaderType::Fragment, desc, &fragShader)))
989 {
990 return nil;
991 }
992 }
993 else
994 {
995 // Non-specialized version
996 fragShader = mFragmentShader;
997 }
998
999 if (!vertShader)
1000 {
1001 // Render pipeline without vertex shader is invalid.
1002 context->handleError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, __FILE__, ANGLE_FUNCTION, __LINE__);
1003 return nil;
1004 }
1005
1006 id<MTLDevice> metalDevice = context->getMetalDevice();
1007
1008 // Convert to Objective-C desc:
1009 AutoObjCObj<MTLRenderPipelineDescriptor> objCDesc = ToObjC(vertShader, fragShader, desc);
1010 // Validate Render Pipeline State:
1011 if (DeviceHasMaximumRenderTargetSize(metalDevice))
1012 {
1013 NSUInteger maxSize = GetMaxRenderTargetSizeForDeviceInBytes(metalDevice);
1014 NSUInteger renderTargetSize =
1015 ComputeTotalSizeUsedForMTLRenderPipelineDescriptor(objCDesc, context, metalDevice);
1016 if (renderTargetSize > maxSize)
1017 {
1018 NSString *errorString =
1019 [NSString stringWithFormat:@"This set of render targets requires %lu bytes of "
1020 @"pixel storage. This device supports %lu bytes.",
1021 (unsigned long)renderTargetSize, (unsigned long)maxSize];
1022 NSError *err = [NSError errorWithDomain:@"MTLValidationError"
1023 code:-1
1024 userInfo:@{NSLocalizedDescriptionKey : errorString}];
1025 context->handleError(err, __FILE__, ANGLE_FUNCTION, __LINE__);
1026 return nil;
1027 }
1028 }
1029 // Special attribute slot for default attribute
1030 if (insertDefaultAttribLayout)
1031 {
1032 MTLVertexBufferLayoutDescriptor *defaultAttribLayoutObjCDesc =
1033 [[MTLVertexBufferLayoutDescriptor alloc] init];
1034 defaultAttribLayoutObjCDesc.stepFunction = MTLVertexStepFunctionConstant;
1035 defaultAttribLayoutObjCDesc.stepRate = 0;
1036 defaultAttribLayoutObjCDesc.stride = kDefaultAttributeSize * kMaxVertexAttribs;
1037
1038 [objCDesc.get().vertexDescriptor.layouts
1039 setObject:[defaultAttribLayoutObjCDesc ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE]
1040 atIndexedSubscript:kDefaultAttribsBindingIndex];
1041 }
1042 // Create pipeline state
1043 NSError *err = nil;
1044 id<MTLRenderPipelineState> newState =
1045 [metalDevice newRenderPipelineStateWithDescriptor:objCDesc error:&err];
1046 if (err)
1047 {
1048 context->handleError(err, __FILE__, ANGLE_FUNCTION, __LINE__);
1049 return nil;
1050 }
1051
1052 return [newState ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1053 }
1054}
1055
1056void RenderPipelineCache::recreatePipelineStates(Context *context)
1057{
1058 for (int hasDefaultAttrib = 0; hasDefaultAttrib <= 1; ++hasDefaultAttrib)
1059 {
1060 for (auto &ite : mRenderPipelineStates[hasDefaultAttrib])
1061 {
1062 if (ite.second == nil)
1063 {
1064 continue;
1065 }
1066
1067 ite.second = createRenderPipelineState(context, ite.first, hasDefaultAttrib);
1068 }
1069 }
1070}

1198
1199AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLComputePipelineState>> ProvokingVertexComputePipelineCache::createComputePipelineState(
1200 Context *context,
1201 const ProvokingVertexComputePipelineDesc &originalDesc)
1202{
1203 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
1204 {
1205 // Disable coverage if the render pipeline's sample count is only 1.
1206 ProvokingVertexComputePipelineDesc desc = originalDesc;
1207
1208 id<MTLFunction> computeFunction = nil;
1209 // Special case for transform feedback shader, we've already created it! See getTransformFeedbackRenderPipeline
1210 if (mSpecializedShaderFactory &&
1211 mSpecializedShaderFactory->hasSpecializedShader(gl::ShaderType::Compute, desc))
1212 {
1213 if (IsError(mSpecializedShaderFactory->getSpecializedShader(
1214 context, gl::ShaderType::Compute, desc, &computeFunction)))
1215 {
1216 return nil;
1217 }
1218 }
1219 else
1220 {
1221 // Non-specialized version
1222 computeFunction = mComputeShader;;
1223 }
1224
1225 if (!computeFunction)
1226 {
1227 // Render pipeline without vertex shader is invalid.
1228 context->handleError(GL_INVALID_OPERATION, __FILE__, ANGLE_FUNCTION, __LINE__);
1229 return nil;
1230 }
1231
1232 id<MTLDevice> metalDevice = context->getMetalDevice();
1233
1234 // Convert to Objective-C desc:
1235 NSError *err = nil;
1236 id<MTLComputePipelineState> newState =
1237 [metalDevice newComputePipelineStateWithFunction:computeFunction error:&err];
1238 if (err)
1239 {
1240 context->handleError(err, __FILE__, ANGLE_FUNCTION, __LINE__);
1241 return nil;
1242 }
1243
1244 return [newState ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1245 }
1246}

1295AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLSamplerState>> StateCache::getSamplerState(id<MTLDevice> metalDevice,
1296 const SamplerDesc &desc)
1297{
1298 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
1299 {
1300 auto ite = mSamplerStates.find(desc);
1301 if (ite == mSamplerStates.end())
1302 {
1303 AutoObjCObj<MTLSamplerDescriptor> objCDesc = ToObjC(desc);
1304 if (!mFeatures.allowRuntimeSamplerCompareMode.enabled)
1305 {
1306 // Runtime sampler compare mode is not supported, fallback to never.
1307 objCDesc.get().compareFunction = MTLCompareFunctionNever;
1308 }
1309 AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLSamplerState>> newState =
1310 [[metalDevice newSamplerStateWithDescriptor:objCDesc] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1311
1312 auto re = mSamplerStates.insert(std::make_pair(desc, newState));
1313 if (!re.second)
1314 return nil;
1315
1316 ite = re.first;
1317 }
1318
1319 return ite->second;
1320 }
